Veteran British actor Sir John Hurt, Oscar-nominated for his star turn in &#8220;The Elephant Man&#8221; and his supporting role in &#8220;Midnight Express&#8221;, has died after a long battle with pancreatic cancer, the BBC reported on Saturday. He was 77.Hurt, who had starred in more than 200 films and television series over a career spanning six decades, revealed in 2015 that he was suffering from the early stages of pancreatic cancer and that he was receiving treatment.The BBC, citing the actor&#8217;s agent, said Hurt had died. Further details of the circumstances of his death were not immediately reported.-Reuters